[[File:Festival of the Nations (2).jpg|thumb|Festival of Nations 2013]] '''Festival of Nations''' is a free, [[multicultural]] public event, held yearly, organized by the International Institute of [[St. Louis]] in [[Tower Grove Park]], a city park on [[Grand Boulevard (St. Louis)|Grand Boulevard]], featuring food booths of many [[Ethnic group|ethnic]] [[cuisine]]s, dance, music, arts, crafts and an international bazaar.<ref name="Home">{{cite web|title=Index|url=http://www.festivalofnationsstl.org/index.html|publisher=The International Institute of St. Louis|accessdate=10 July 2011}}</ref>
==History== The International Institute of St. Louis Organized the International May Festival in [[St. Louis]] in 1920. Approximately 2,000 people attended the May Festival. The May Festival was one of the earliest multicultural celebrations in the US and today's Festival of Nations originated from the May Festival. <ref name="History">{{cite web|title=Media|url=http://www.festivalofnationsstl.org/media.html|publisher=The International Institute of St. Louis|accessdate=10 July 2011}}</ref>
==IISTL== The International Institute of St. Louis is involved in building positive relationships between new comers ([[immigrants]]) and long time [[Americans]]. The institute provides various services including teaching English, resettling refugees, helping new comers find jobs and providing translation & other servies. <ref name="iistl">{{cite web|title=iistl index|url=http://www.iistl.org/index.html|publisher=The International Institute of St. Louis|accessdate=10 July 2011}}</ref>
==Festival of Nations 2010 Celebration== The celebrations were held on Aug 28 & 29th in [[Tower Grove Park]]. An estimated 140,000 visitors attended. <ref name="2010 celebration">{{cite web|title=FonwrapupPR10.pdf|url=http://www.festivalofnationsstl.org/pdf/FonwrapupPR10.pdf|publisher=The International Institute of St. Louis|accessdate=10 July 2011}}</ref>
==Festival of Nations 2011 Celebration== The celebrations are to be held on Aug 27 & 28th in Tower Grove Park. 125 community organizations are expected to participate. Music and dance by traditional ethnic artists all over the world will be performed. 50 food booths and 40 gift booths will be selling food and gifts. <ref name="2011 celebration">{{cite web|title=FoN%20Fact%20Sheet%202011.pdf|url=http://www.festivalofnationsstl.org/pdf/FoN%20Fact%20Sheet%202011.pdf|publisher=The International Institute of St. Louis|accessdate=10 July 2011}}</ref>
==External links== * {{cite web|url= http://www.festivalofnationsstl.org/pdf/FonwrapupPR10.pdf |title="2010 Festival of Nations is a wrap" }}&nbsp;{{small|(90&nbsp;KB)}} * {{cite web|url= http://www.festivalofnationsstl.org/pdf/FoN%20Fact%20Sheet%202011.pdf |title="Festival of Nations - A grand global gathering" }}&nbsp;{{small|(154&nbsp;KB)}}
